sentences: Evaluna Mercedes Reglero Rodríguez de Echeverry (born August 7, 1997), known as Evaluna Montaner, is a Venezuelan actress,singer and music director, daughter of singer Ricardo Montaner and younger sister of Mauricio and Ricardo Montaner, known as Mau y Ricky.
In 2020, she married her boyfriend of five years, the Colombian singer Camilo Echeverry.
In 2020, she married her boyfriend of five years, the Colombian singer Camilo Echeverry.
In October 2021, the couple announced that they're expecting their first child.

In 2012, Evaluna's father Ricardo Montaner chose to sing the Christian ballad La Gloria de Dios (The Glory of God), in addition to taking her on the tours of Frequent Flyer Tour, which began her career as a singer.
Si existe (If it exists) was the name of her first single released in December 2013, made with the help of her mother, the Venezuelan Marlene Rodriguez.
